üóÇÔ∏è Database Name: libraryDB
Collection Name: books

üß© 1. Create / Insert Documents (C - Create)
use libraryDB

// Insert single document
db.books.insertOne({
  _id: 1,
  title: "Database System Concepts",
  author: "Silberschatz",
  price: 550,
  available: true,
  category: "DBMS"
})

// Insert multiple documents
db.books.insertMany([
  { _id: 2, title: "Operating Systems", author: "Galvin", price: 600, available: true, category: "OS" },
  { _id: 3, title: "Computer Networks", author: "Tanenbaum", price: 700, available: false, category: "Networking" },
  { _id: 4, title: "Data Structures", author: "Narasimha", price: 400, available: true, category: "DSA" }
])

üîç 2. Read / Query Documents (R - Read)
// Display all documents
db.books.find().pretty()

// Find specific document
db.books.find({ title: "Operating Systems" })

// Find with condition
db.books.find({ price: { $gt: 500 } })

// Find using logical operators
db.books.find({ $or: [ { price: { $lt: 500 } }, { available: false } ] })

‚úèÔ∏è 3. Update Documents (U - Update)
// Update a single document
db.books.updateOne(
  { _id: 4 },
  { $set: { price: 450 } }
)

// Update multiple documents
db.books.updateMany(
  { available: true },
  { $set: { category: "Computer Science" } }
)

‚ùå 4. Delete Documents (D - Delete)
// Delete one document
db.books.deleteOne({ title: "Operating Systems" })

// Delete multiple documents
db.books.deleteMany({ available: false })

üíæ 5. SAVE Method (Upsert Functionality)
// save() replaces or inserts a document
db.books.save({
  _id: 5,
  title: "Artificial Intelligence",
  author: "Russell",
  price: 800,
  available: true,
  category: "AI"
})


üßÆ 6. Display Final Collection
db.books.find().pretty()
